text.section:
The code of student rights and responsibilities adopted by the committee may define rights and responsibilities regarding, but not limited to, the following:
Right of expression, including, but not limited to, appearance, assembly, association, and circulation of petitions and literature;
Right to participate in decision-making procedures directly affecting students;
Right to procedural due process concerning major disciplinary action, as defined by the code;
Right to receive academic grades based only upon academic performance;
Right to freedom from abuse and threat of abuse by members of school faculties and administration personnel; and
Right of access by a student to his or her own records and guarantee of the confidentiality of a student's academic records outside of the school system, except upon written authorization of the student or his or her parents or guardians.
